description:
&lt;p&gt;T&lt;span&gt;his is an exciting time for Leicester’s Hospitals. &lt;/span&gt;The UHL Becoming the Best Transformation Programme Team has recently been established within the Trust to ensure the integration of quality, performance and efficiency, and to deliver the Financial Recovery Plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will provide essential support to the Becoming the Best Transformation team, supporting the successful delivery of associated programmes and workstreams. They will be required to engage with internal clinical and managerial teams and will provide the structure, governance process and critical challenge for the programme of work undertaken. Also, they will report on progress, key issues and risks to enable key decisions and actions to be taken in a timely manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, motivated and organised individual who has project experience and is looking for a challenge.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;With our clear vision to provide Caring at its Best, our strong values, ambitious quality improvement plans and transformation agenda, there’s never been a better time to join University Hospitals of Leicester NHS Trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ben Shaw - Director of Productivity and Efficiency&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ben.Shaw@uhl-tr.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07789 904081&lt;/p&gt;
